Ọbẹ̀ Ọ̀gbọ̀nọ̀ (Igbo: bush mango, Yorùbá: Àpọ̀n) jẹ́ ọbẹ̀ kan ní ilẹ̀ Nàìjíríà tí wọ́n ń sè pẹ̀lú èso àpọ̀n gbị́́gbẹ (the local name for Irvingia seeds),[1] àti àwọn ǹ kan óṇ́jẹ ìbílẹ̀ mìíràn. 
Àpọ̀n lílọ̀ náà má ń fún ọbẹ̀ ní àwọ̀ dúdú. Yàtọ̀ sí kúrú Àpọ̀n yìí, wọ́n tún ma ń fi omi, epo, ata gígún, ẹran àti àwọn ohun tó lè mú ọbẹ̀ dùn si. Wọ́n tún lè fi àwọn ẹ̀fọ́ bíi:[1] ẹ̀fọ́ gbúre, ẹ̀fọ́ ewúro, ẹ̀fọ́ ṣọkọ tàbí tẹ̀tẹ̀. 
Wọ́n tún lè fi ilá, tìmọ́ọ̀tì, àlùbọ́sà àti irú si kì ò lè dùn dára dára. 
Bạ́kan náà, àwọn ẹran bí: Ògúnfe, ẹran adìyẹ, ẹran àgbò, edé, ẹran ìgbẹ́, ni wọ́n tún lè fi gbé ọbẹ̀ náà là́rugẹ.[1] Wọ́n lè jẹ ọbẹ̀ náà pẹ̀lú Fùfú, Ẹ̀bà, Iyán, Sẹ̀mò́, Túwó, Àpárán, Àmàlà Láfún tàbị́ Gbódo àti bẹ́ẹ̀ bẹ́ẹ̀ lọ. 
Ṣùgbọ́n wọ́n kìí fi jẹ óúnjẹ bi Búrẹ́dì, ìrẹsì, ẹ̀wà,[1] nítorí yíyọ̀ tàbí fífà tì ò ma ń fà bí ọbẹ̀ Ilá. 
