Mionga ki Ôbo (tàbí Mionga ki Ôbo: Mar e Selva) ni fíìmù ti ọdún 2002 kan tí wọ́n ṣe lórílẹ̀-èdè São Tomé and Príncipe, tí olùdarí rẹ̀ n ṣe Ângelo Torres [1] tí Luis Correia àti Noé Mendelle síì dì jọ ṣe àgbéjáde rẹ̀ láti ilé-iṣẹ́ LX Filmes.[2][3] 
Fíìmù náà dá lóri ìrìn-àjò àwọn olùgbé àtijọ́ ti erékùsù São Tomé tí wọ́n pè ní Angolares.[1] Wọ́n jẹ́ àwọn ìran Àngólà tí ó yè níbi jàmbá ọkọ̀ ojú-omi kan tí ó ṣẹlẹ̀ ní ọdún 1540.[2][3] Fíìmù náà jẹ́ ọ̀kan nínu àwọn fíìmù tí wọ́n gbéṣe gbogbo ètò rẹ̀ lórílẹ̀-èdè São Tomé and Príncipe.[4] 
