Evelyn Badu tí a bí ní ọjọ́ kọkànlá Oṣù Kẹ̀sán ọdún 2003) jẹ́ agbábọ́ọ̀lù ọmọ orílẹ̀-ède Ghana kan tí ó ń ṣeré gẹ́gẹ́ bíi agbábọ́ọ̀lù fún ẹgbẹ́ agbábọ́ọ̀lù Avaldsnes IL ti Norway àti ẹgbẹ́ agbábọ́ọ̀lù obìnrin Ghana . 
Isẹ́ ẹgbẹ́ agbábọ́ọ̀lù 
Badu ti gbábọ́ọ̀lù fún Hasaacas Ladies ní Ghana, tí ó sì farahàn ní bi ìdíje ìparí ìdíje Women's Champions League ti CAF ní ọdún 2021 . Ó kó lọ sí ẹgbẹ́ agbábọ́ọ̀lù Avaldsnes IL fún àkókò 2022. [1] 
Isẹ́ Òkè Òkun 
Badu jẹ́ apákan ti ẹgbẹ́ agbábọ́ọ̀lù Ghana tí ó díje nínú ìdíjeFIFA U-20 Women's World Cupti ọdún 2018, ṣùgbọ́n kò kópa nínú eré kankan. Ó wà ní ìpele gíga ní àkókò ìdíje CAF Women's Olympic Qualifying Tournamentti ọdún 2020 ( Ìsí kẹta ). 
